{"id": 65, "ts": 1778939193.9140701, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_1", "message": "After reviewing all the available attributes for each candidate, I see the following picture:\n**Candidate\u202fA** \u2013 Strong technical foresight (danger anticipation, excellent spatial vision, ability to see complex connections) and good leadership, but his difficulty accepting criticism and being unorganized raise concerns for crew coordination on long\u2011haul flights. No data on calmness, decision speed, or crew\u2011communication strengths beyond leadership.\n**Candidate\u202fB** \u2013 Very conscientious (high reliability), handles stress well (calm under sustained workload), assesses weather accurately and has excellent computer skills (critical for long\u2011distance flight planning). The only downsides are a grumpy, sometimes uncooperative attitude and a pretentious tone, which are communication issues but not shown to impair safety directly.\n**Candidate\u202fC** \u2013 100\u202f% reliable, makes quick correct decisions, stays calm in a crisis and creates a positive crew atmosphere, putting others\u2019 concerns first. However, he has difficulty communicating ideas, is regarded as egocentric, and is not eager to pursue further education\u2014traits that could hinder teamwork and long\u2011term professional development.\n**Candidate\u202fD** \u2013 Excellent problem\u2011solving, concentration, and a strong sense of responsibility, plus the ability to respond adequately to unexpected events. Yet he is seen as arrogant, has weak leadership, and is described as moody/loner, which are serious drawbacks for sustained crew cooperation.\nBalancing the selection criteria\u2014reliability, technical competence, calmness under pressure, sound decision\u2011making, and teamwork\u2014the profile that best fits a long\u2011distance pilot is **Candidate\u202fB**. His reliability, stress resilience, and technical skills outweigh the manageable communication weaknesses, whereas the other candidates each have a more critical deficit (A\u2019s teamwork gaps, C\u2019s communication and development reluctance, D\u2019s leadership/arrogance issues).\n**Vote:** Candidate\u202fB\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
